===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|upbreiden}}, from {{m|ang|upp||up}} + {{m|ang|bregdan||to draw, twist, weave; the kindred}}. Compare {{etyl|is|-}} {{m|is|bregða||to draw, brandish, braid, deviate from, change, break off, upbraid}}. See {{term|up}}, and {{term|braid}} {{qualifier|transitive}}.

